\pard\f0\fs28  Subgen. {\b Ladanum} Reichenb. Vegetative parts, bracteoles and calyx with soft, crispate or patent hairs, and frequently also with glandular hairs, but without rigid yellowish hairs; stem 4-angled or terete, not swollen at the nodes.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 1. G. segetum} Necker, {\i Hist. Comment. Acad. Elect. Theod-. Palat.}{\b  2}: 474 (1770) ({\i G. dubia} Leers). Stem up to 50 cm, 4-angled, with crispate hairs and glandular hairs. Leaves lanceolate to ovate, dentate, cuneate at the base, subacute. Calyx 7-10 mm, green, densely and softly patent-hairy with smooth hairs, glandular. Corolla (20-)25-30(-35) mm, pale yellow, rarely lilac, with purple blotches. 2n = 16.{\i  Calcifuge. •  From Wales and N.E. Spain eastwards to Denmark and N.E. Italy}. Be Br Da Ga Ge He Ho Hs It [Au Cz Hu Ju Rm].
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28   {\b  2. G. pyrenaica} Bartl., {\i Ind. Sem. Horti Goetting.}{\b  1848}: 4 (1848). Stems up to 40 cm, sometimes very dwarf, 4-angled, with soft crispate hairs and glandular hairs. Leaves ovate to deltate-ovate, dentate, truncate or subcordate at base; apex very obtuse. Calyx 8-10 mm, green, with dense, smooth, soft, patent hairs. Corolla 17-25 mm, pinkish-purple, usually with darker blotches. 2n = 16.{\i  Sandy or gravelly ground by mountain streams; calcifuge. • E. Pyrenees.} Ga Hs.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28   {\b  3. G. ladanum} L., {\i Sp. Pl.} 579 (1753) ({\i G. intermedia} Vill.). Stem up to 40 cm, with crispate hairs and patent, glandular hairs. Leaves ovate-lanceolate to broadly ovate, dentate, cuneate to subtruncate (rarely attenuate) at the base. Calyx 8-12 mm, green, with smooth or finely punctate, patent, translucent hairs. Corolla 15-28 mm, deep pink with yellow blotches. 2n = 16.{\i  Somewhat calcifuge. Most of Europe except the islands and the extreme south.} Al Au Be Bu Co Cz Da Fe Ga Ge He Ho Hs Hu It Ju  No Po Rm Rs (N, B, C, W, K, E) Su.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28   {\b  4. G. angustifolia} Ehrh. ex Hoffm.,{\i  Deutschl. Fl.} ed. 2, {\b 2}: 8 (1804) ({\i G. ladanum} subsp.{\i  angustifolia} Gaudin, G. ladanum sensu Coste, non L.). Stem up to 40 cm, with crispate hairs, with or without glandular hairs. Leaves narrowly linear to lanceolate-ovate or rarely ovate, entire or dentate, rarely glabrous, cuneate at base. Calyx 8-13 mm; tube canescent to villous with strongly papillose, opaque hairs. Corolla 14-24 mm, deep reddish-pink with yellow blotches (rarely white). 2n = 16. {\i W., C. & S. Europe, eastwards to Poland and Bulgaria.} Au Be Br Bu Cz *Da Ga Ge He Ho Hs Hu It Ju Po Rm [Hb Su].
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28   {\b  5. G. reuteri} Reichenb. fil., {\i Icon. Fl. Germ.}{\b  18}: 17 (1856). Stem up to c. 80 cm, wiry, glabrous or with very short, appressed hairs, especially above. Leaves lanceolate to almost linear, dentate, subacute, attenuate at base. Calyx 9-15 mm, appressed-hairy and sometimes shortly glandular. Corolla 10-20 mm, deep pink (rarely white), with yellow blotches.{\i  Dry screes and rocks.• Maritime Alps.} Ga It.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28  Perhaps only a subspecies of {\b 4}.
\par

